Git Tags
========
Tagging is done to mark some release points.
Mark historic point for your project using tags.


Commands
=========
git checkout branch_name
git tag -a v1.1 -m "added a release tag."(annotative tag)
git show v1.0
git tag -l
git tag -d tag_name
git tag tag_name
git push origin tag_name
git push origin --tags
git push origin -d tag_name
git checkout -b branch_name tag_name
git tag tag_name commit_ref

Tags are created to mark historic points.

git push origin --delete branch_name
git commit --amend
git diff curent_branch origin/branch
git log -1 HEAD --stat
